Receiving a funding amount of $19.91 million, the Agriculture sector experienced a decline from $95.80 million. It's crucial to be aware of these potential negative impacts and adopt healthy technology habits.

Meaningful gifts for Mid-Autumn Festival
Mid-Autumn Festival not only brings people closer together but is also an opportunity for people to express their appreciation to each other through meaningful Mid-Autumn Festival gifts. Gifts are sent with messages expressing love and respect, bringing joy and happiness to the recipient as well as the giver. And below are some suggestions for choosing a meaningful and memorable gift during the Mid-Autumn Festival.

Giving away moon cakes

Mooncakes have a humanistic meaning and are associated with the tradition of love and attachment of Vietnamese people for thousands of years. A beautiful box of moon cakes carries a deep gratitude to the recipient. More specifically, if on this day, you make moon cakes yourself to give to relatives or friends, it shows your heart and sincerity to that person. What could be more special and meaningful than being able to eat moon cakes with your family, drink thick tea, and have a feast in the cool, peaceful autumn weather?
Buy toys, make Mid-Autumn lanterns

According to ancient Vietnamese customs, every Mid-Autumn Festival night, people in the village organize together to make lanterns, lion dances,... very fun. These days, when the Mid-Autumn Festival has become familiar and become a spiritual dish for Vietnamese people, especially for children, the most meaningful thing you can do for your children is to buy toys for them. Make your own Mid-Autumn lanterns or take them out to enjoy the full moon festival, watch lion dances, etc. On this occasion, let the children have the opportunity to enjoy carrying lanterns, sing, entertain, and eat candies freely. instead of being limited to weekdays.
Tell the story of the Mid-Autumn Festival

You can tell stories about the Mid-Autumn Festival to everyone, especially those who are parents. This also creates interest in the mysterious stories about Uncle Cuoi, the genus Hang, the moon,... - things that children may have heard about but do not fully understand. Children will certainly feel interested in what they hear and learn many things through those stories.

Mid-Autumn Festival song

Familiar songs about the Mid-Autumn Festival will stir up a happy and exciting atmosphere for everyone. Some good and meaningful songs such as Mid-Autumn Festival Lantern Procession, I Go to Lantern Parade, Full Moon Festival, Full Moon Night Dream,... will evoke nostalgic emotions in listeners, remembering their peaceful childhood under the full moon light. with my little friends
Watch the moon with loved ones

On the full moon night of August every year, the moon will be fullest and brightest. Therefore, going with relatives and friends to watch the moon and pray for the best things for each other on Mid-Autumn Festival night is an extremely meaningful thing.

Sweet and meaningful wishes

Besides the joys of Mid-Autumn Festival, don't forget to give each other the sweetest and most meaningful wishes. Perhaps on weekdays people have few opportunities to express their feelings, so on special occasions like this, let's give each other small but meaningful words, wishes or actions, enough to make them happy. understand your sincerity.
